				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Signature (4 bytes) "NES",0x1B?</div><br /><br />Changing the file signature will kill backward compatibility.<br /><br />If we want the ROM to load in older emus, it <em>must</em> look just like a regular iNES file.<br /><br />I really think a secondary signature is the way to go here.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">By incorporating SRAM in the "ROM", it'll reduce file clutter and unofficially allow trainers to be incorporated into SRAM loading</div>
<br />
<br />I don't really like the idea of "SRAM ROM" or trainers.  RAM on the cartridge is just that -- RAM.  Putting RAM in a ROM image doesn't really make a lot of sense.  And ROM for iNES trainers aren't even <em>on</em> the cartridge and probably should be excluded all around.</div>

